</title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/3097/how-do-i-add-icons-to-the-status-bar/?comment=5009#comment-5009</link><description>Can you please share your config files? Thanks!</description><pubDate>Mon, 24 Nov 2014 23:32:25 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/3097/how-do-i-add-icons-to-the-status-bar/?comment=5009#comment-5009</guid></item><item><title>Answer by memeplex for &lt;p&gt;I would like to add icons to the i3 status bar but I don't want to patch i3bar.&lt;/p&gt;
 </title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/3097/how-do-i-add-icons-to-the-status-bar/?answer=3098#post-id-3098</link><description>You can use one of the impressive iconic true type font sets that are around the web to get nice looking monochromatic icons in your i3 status bar without having to patch it at all.

For Arch users there are detailed instructions in http://wiki.archlinux.org/index.php/I3#Iconic_fonts_in_the_status_bar. For users of other distros it's as simple as getting the correct ttf files (you can easily figure out how to do that by looking at the PKGBUILD files for Arch) and putting them under /usr/share/fonts/TTF or any location where your ttf fonts happen to be. From that point on everything stated for Arch applies ditto to any distro.</description><pubDate>Wed, 25 Dec 2013 17:22:11 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/3097/how-do-i-add-icons-to-the-status-bar/?answer=3098#post-id-3098</guid></item><item><title>Answer by Licaon_Kter for &lt;p&gt;I would like to add icons to the i3 status bar but I don't want to patch i3bar.&lt;/p&gt;
